* Detailed command-line options

  -A <android-sdk-path>
  --android-sdk <android-sdk-path>

  specify path to android sdk, if not specified agrab looks for environmental
  variable ANDROID_SDK to look for path to android sdk. finally, falls down to
  search through the PATH variable.

  -s <android-emulator-serial>
  --serial <android-emulator-serial>

  specify the serial to identify a running android-emulator. if not specified,
  assumes that there is a default adb connection established.

  -o <output-file-path>
  --output <output-file-path>

  specify the output file path. the extension of output file determines the
  media container format, if extension is absent 'mp4' format is used.

  NOTE: currently, there is no option to set the encoder to be used, it is
        hard-coded to mpeg4

  -L
  --live

  turn on live streaming through rtmp, requires ffmpeg to be built with
  librtmp support
